ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: My biggest fear is of becoming fat.
Notes: 1 = very untrue; 2 = somewhat untrue; 3 = somewhat true; 4 = very true

ElementDescription: I am afraid to gain even a little weight.
Notes: 1 = very untrue; 2 = somewhat untrue; 3 = somewhat true; 4 = very true

ElementDescription: I believe that there is a real risk that I will become  overweight someday.
Notes: 1 = very untrue; 2 = somewhat untrue; 3 = somewhat true; 4 = very true

ElementDescription: I don't understand how overweight people can live with themselves.
Notes: 1 = very untrue; 2 = somewhat untrue; 3 = somewhat true; 4 = very true

ElementDescription: Becoming fat would be the worst thing that could happen to me.
Notes: 1 = very untrue; 2 = somewhat untrue; 3 = somewhat true; 4 = very true

ElementDescription: If I stopped concentrating on controlling my weight; chances are that I would become very fat.
Notes: 1 = very untrue; 2 = somewhat untrue; 3 = somewhat true; 4 = very true

ElementDescription: There is nothing that I can do to make the thought of gaining weight less painful and frightening.
Notes: 1 = very untrue; 2 = somewhat untrue; 3 = somewhat true; 4 = very true

ElementDescription: I feel like all my energy goes into controlling my weight.
Notes: 1 = very untrue; 2 = somewhat untrue; 3 = somewhat true; 4 = very true

ElementDescription: If I eat even a little. I may lose control and not stop eating.
Notes: 1 = very untrue; 2 = somewhat untrue; 3 = somewhat true; 4 = very true

ElementDescription: Staying hungry is the only way I can guard against losing control and becoming fat.
Notes: 1 = very untrue; 2 = somewhat untrue; 3 = somewhat true; 4 = very true

ElementDescription: Goldfarb Fear of Fat Total Score
Notes: 10 = No fear of fat ; 40 = Extreme fear of fat
